githubInfo.description: The easiest way to use Unicode Emoji in Scala🎉✨
githubInfo.readme:
emojipolation

A Emoji Interpolation Library for Scala☺️✨

Usage

Add dependency in your Build.sbt👇

libraryDependencies += "io.github.todokr" %% "emojipolation" % "0.2.0"

Usage is very simple💃

import io.github.todokr.Emojipolation._
emoji":baby: you can drive my :car: :dash:" 
// 👶 you can drive my 🚗 💨

emojipolation is using emoji-java which is nice emoji library for Java internally, so you can use same emojis and aliases.

Fitzpatrick modifiers

Fitzpatrick modifiers are supported.

emoji":boy|type_3: & :girl|type_1_2: & :information_desk_person|type_4:"
// 👦🏼 & 👧🏻 & 💁🏽
Modifier Type
🏻 type_1_2
🏼 type_3
🏽 type_4
🏾 type_5
🏿 type_6
